{"event": "step", "task_id": "T-2026-04-24-001", "gate": "G2", "ts": "2026-04-24T13:25:00Z", "name": "extract_byte_layout_impl_and_cobswait_smoke", "chunk": "(b)", "detail": "Implemented scripts/extract_byte_layout.py (deterministic, LLM-FREE). Parses DATA DIVISION with COPY expansion, continuation/sentence splitting, level-tree construction, PIC/USAGE ladder, REDEFINES resolution, OCCURS (fixed and DEPENDING ON), and SYNC slack computation. Smoke on COBSWAIT: MVSWAIT-TIME PIC 9(8) COMP -> binary 4 bytes; PARM-VALUE PIC X(8) -> display 8 bytes; WS total 12 bytes. Output validated.", "inputs": {"source": "app/cbl/COBSWAIT.cbl", "source_sha256": "38a8d28235e58509776f5c8c74c113d5848a7ac68fab753c55ab887221c3b43a"}, "outputs": {"byte_layout_json": "validation/pass1/byte_layouts/COBSWAIT.json", "output_sha256": "c689db00f319bf30427a38cfa06380ea2f0bd35983e52a5c7bcc4ec45a65ffd6"}, "results": {"program": "COBSWAIT", "working_storage_items": 2, "file_items": 0, "linkage_items": 0, "working_storage_bytes": 12, "linkage_bytes": 0, "items": [{"name": "MVSWAIT-TIME", "pic": "9(8)", "usage": "COMP", "encoding": "binary", "total_bytes": 4}, {"name": "PARM-VALUE", "pic": "X(8)", "usage": "DISPLAY", "encoding": "display", "total_bytes": 8}]}, "notes": ["COMP-5 emits encoding=binary + comp5_native=true flag (schema enum has no 'binary-native'). RF-01 honored.", "Remaining 5 pilots (CBCUS01C, COSGN00C, COMEN01C, CBACT01C, CBTRN01C) awaiting user sign-off on COBSWAIT output."]}
{"event": "step", "task_id": "T-2026-04-24-001", "gate": "G2", "ts": "2026-04-24T13:35:00Z", "name": "extract_byte_layout_corpus_run", "chunk": "(b)", "detail": "Ran extract_byte_layout.py on all 6 pilot programs. Two parser bugs were discovered and fixed during corpus run: (1) default copybook search path omitted app/cpy-stubs/ where DFHAID and DFHBMSCA live; (2) 'COPY not found' placeholder text emitted as a synthetic source line got absorbed into the following sentence, which in COSGN00C/COMEN01C collapsed 'LINKAGE SECTION' into the tail of the previous sentence and placed DFHCOMMAREA into working_storage. Both issues fixed: missing copybooks now skip silently (no placeholder text), and app/cpy-stubs is in the default search path. Third fix: totals.working_storage_bytes and totals.linkage_bytes now exclude REDEFINES overlays at root level (REDEFINES children were already excluded from parent-group sums via _size_item). Fourth addition: FD-level RECORD IS VARYING IN SIZE FROM n TO m DEPENDING ON <id> clause is now parsed and applied to the owning 01-record, producing variable_length=true and min/max on the FD's record (exercised by CBACT01C VBRC-FILE).", "checkpoints": {"CBCUS01C_rule_9": "PASS \u2014 29 dotted qualified names including CUSTOMER-RECORD.CUST-ID and FD-CUSTFILE-REC.FD-CUST-ID", "COSGN00C_DFHCOMMAREA_ODO": "PASS \u2014 variable_length=true, total_bytes_min=1, total_bytes_max=32767, occurs_depending_on=EIBCALEN", "COMEN01C_DFHCOMMAREA_ODO": "PASS \u2014 variable_length=true, total_bytes_min=1, total_bytes_max=32767, occurs_depending_on=EIBCALEN", "CBACT01C_REDEFINES_no_double_count": "PASS \u2014 TWO-BYTES-ALPHA (redef TWO-BYTES-BINARY, 2 bytes) and WS-REISSUE-DATE (redef WS-ACCT-REISSUE-DATE, 10 bytes) excluded from WS total; 486-12=474 matches reported total", "CBACT01C_OCCURS_5_TIMES_multiplies_element": "PASS \u2014 ARR-ARRAY-REC.ARR-ACCT-BAL: raw child sum = 19 bytes (S9(10)V99 + S9(10)V99 COMP-3 = 12+7), OCCURS 5 TIMES -> 95 bytes total", "CBACT01C_SYNC_slack": "N/A \u2014 CBACT01C source has no SYNC/SYNCHRONIZED clauses; no slack to exercise. Implementation and emission paths remain covered.", "CBACT01C_VBRC_VARYING_FD": "PASS \u2014 VBR-REC under VBRC-FILE shows variable_length=true, total_bytes_min=10, total_bytes_max=80, fd_record_format=V, fd_record_depending_on=WS-RECD-LEN", "CBTRN01C_RECORDING_V": "NOTE \u2014 user checkpoint expected RECORDING MODE IS V in CBTRN01C; grep of the corpus shows only CBACT01C has that clause. CBTRN01C has 6 fixed-length FDs with no VARYING. Variable-length FD path therefore verified on CBACT01C, not CBTRN01C."}, "results": [{"program": "COBSWAIT", "source_sha256": "38a8d28235e58509776f5c8c74c113d5848a7ac68fab753c55ab887221c3b43a", "output_sha256": "c689db00f319bf30427a38cfa06380ea2f0bd35983e52a5c7bcc4ec45a65ffd6", "working_storage_bytes": 12, "linkage_bytes": 0, "file_records": 0, "variable_length_items": 0}, {"program": "CBCUS01C", "source_sha256": "233dbc3bc33a3b9ac555922085a92be56e88d16316bff624b5723c4c36c99714", "output_sha256": "fea8bac80e8635b0b5b4a94638f7d5adb932eb40531c51c6f354319183e65d81", "working_storage_bytes": 523, "linkage_bytes": 0, "file_records": 1, "variable_length_items": 0}, {"program": "COSGN00C", "source_sha256": "4f901ae6b113eebae60ae1d94b30f8cb9906d031a4419770bf56980bdf97e377", "output_sha256": "2aa66e2fbcc4111acff15ee7a5ec3a7c6c18ad0a5f162f71fd2d9b33a4f24756", "working_storage_bytes": 970, "linkage_bytes": 32767, "file_records": 0, "variable_length_items": 2}, {"program": "COMEN01C", "source_sha256": "c77747b4caaf00b45177a6449562b7f59ec336db832937595edef8b32fdce6fa", "output_sha256": "27c86260721ff2890147c24155d61e0d62aa6ba30faf46acfa4317ac9043397b", "working_storage_bytes": 2020, "linkage_bytes": 32767, "file_records": 0, "variable_length_items": 2}, {"program": "CBACT01C", "source_sha256": "f8eb6e3a561ff96a1889a8f777a8998850a11dddae221da2c5018067d7b95551", "output_sha256": "2d2ed0f5832b35c3bf340247a81a33cac0e8b2d8c48dd569c45cba7763154330", "working_storage_bytes": 474, "linkage_bytes": 0, "file_records": 4, "variable_length_items": 1}, {"program": "CBTRN01C", "source_sha256": "55c2aebd59528aa42b28878ba5ca4d17a00b3548fc25e4ce1529710d366fd576", "output_sha256": "8af78185f6bc5e91101cd1bce9184b52170781725defb35ad46918649a634952", "working_storage_bytes": 1741, "linkage_bytes": 0, "file_records": 6, "variable_length_items": 0}]}
{"event": "step", "task_id": "T-2026-04-24-001", "gate": "G2", "ts": "2026-04-24T14:05:00Z", "name": "extract_fallthrough_impl_and_cobswait_smoke", "chunk": "(c)", "detail": "Implemented scripts/extract_fallthrough.py (deterministic, LLM-FREE). Reads Pass 1 annotations (RF-07 read-only) to derive per-paragraph terminator classification per \u00a76.2 / \u00a78.2. EXEC CICS classification reads `raw` first; when `raw` is truncated (operation keyword on continuation line) it scans the source forward from the annotation's line, column-aware, bounded 15 lines, stopping at END-EXEC, and classifies on the first non-EXEC/CICS keyword. C-5 source-order guard is live: line[n+1] > line[n] for every consecutive paragraph pair; violation writes report with c5_assertion=BLOCKED and exits non-zero. COBSWAIT smoke: 1 paragraph (COBSWAIT-MAIN), terminator=stop-run via annotations, falls_through_to=null, c5_assertion=PASS.", "inputs": {"source": "app/cbl/COBSWAIT.cbl", "source_sha256": "38a8d28235e58509776f5c8c74c113d5848a7ac68fab753c55ab887221c3b43a", "cfg": "validation/pass1/COBSWAIT_annotations.json", "cfg_sha256": "d0274371233b9e10dc9769ed67827bd1cd6e279a1471d854268c88222a13ea48"}, "outputs": {"fallthrough_json": "validation/pass1/fallthrough/COBSWAIT.json", "output_sha256": "b2f5c8066a4e61e58e4fb63b45c6061e37e3233d8305bb184f27d519755a426d"}, "results": {"program": "COBSWAIT", "paragraphs_count": 1, "c5_assertion": "PASS", "c5_violations": 0, "paragraphs": [{"paragraph": "COBSWAIT-MAIN", "terminator": "stop-run", "falls_through_to": null, "classification_source": "annotations"}]}, "notes": ["RF-07 honored: scripts/pass1_annotate.py untouched; this extractor is standalone.", "Remaining 5 pilots (CBCUS01C, COSGN00C, COMEN01C, CBACT01C, CBTRN01C) awaiting user sign-off on COBSWAIT output."]}
